    impact: '''Samudra Manthan memulihkan kekuasaan para dewa atas tiga dunia dan melahirkan banyak entitas kosmis penting: Lakshmi menjadi permaisuri Wisnu, Dhanvantari menjadi bapak ilmu pengobatan Ayurveda, dan Rahu-Ketu menjadi penyebab abadi gerhana matahari dan bulan. Peristiwa ini juga menetapkan Nilakantha sebagai gelar suci Siwa. Persaingan dewa-Asura yang ditegaskan di sini menjadi pola berulang dalam banyak kisah Purana selanjutnya, sementara amrita yang diperebutkan meneguhkan batas abadi antara yang fana dan yang kekal.''',
    impactEn: '''The Churning of the Ocean restored the gods\' rule over the three worlds and produced many vital cosmic entities: Lakshmi became Vishnu\'s consort, Dhanvantari became the father of Ayurvedic medicine, and Rahu-Ketu became the eternal cause of solar and lunar eclipses. The event also established Nilakantha as a sacred epithet of Shiva. The Deva-Asura rivalry affirmed here became a recurring pattern in many later Puranic tales, while the contested amrita reinforced the eternal boundary between the mortal and the immortal.''',
    meaning: '''Samudra Manthan melambangkan proses spiritual mengaduk batin manusia: kerja keras dan kesabaran (pengadukan) yang harus dilalui sebelum racun (Halahala, lambang keserakahan dan kegelapan batin) dihadapi dan diatasi terlebih dahulu, barulah nektar keabadian (kebijaksanaan tertinggi) dapat diraih. Kerja sama sementara antara dewa dan Asura mengajarkan bahwa kebaikan dan kejahatan kadang harus bersinergi demi tujuan besar. Kisah ini juga menegaskan peran Wisnu sebagai penjaga tatanan kosmis melalui berbagai awatara-Nya.''',
    meaningEn: '''The Churning of the Ocean symbolizes the spiritual process of churning the inner self: the labor and patience (the churning) that must be endured before the poison (Halahala, representing greed and inner darkness) is faced and overcome, only then can the nectar of immortality (supreme wisdom) be attained. The temporary cooperation between gods and demons teaches that good and evil must sometimes work together toward a greater purpose. The tale also affirms Vishnu\'s role as guardian of cosmic order through his many avatars.''',
