    meaningEn: '''The tale of Durga versus Mahishasura symbolizes the triumph of the divine feminine power, Shakti, over an evil that dismissed and underestimated women as a threat. Durga\'s creation from the combined energy of all the gods affirms that true strength arises from unity rather than individualism. Mahishasura\'s repeated shape-shifting symbolizes the cunning nature of evil, forever hiding behind different masks, yet ultimately never able to escape the persistent divine justice that confronts it.''',
